  "local_port": 47122,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there any good placement at northern India engineering college?",
  "response": "Yes, **Northern India Engineering College (NIEC)** has shown decent placement records over the years, especially for engineering and technical programs. NIEC is affiliated with **Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University (GGSIPU)** for its undergraduate and postgraduate programs, and it has been recognized for its placement efforts. Here are some key points about placements at NIEC:\n\n### 1. **Placement Statistics**\n   - **Placement Rate**: The placement rate varies yearly but generally ranges between **70% to 85%** for engineering students.\n   - **Top Recruiters**: Companies like **TCS, Infosys, Wipro, Capgemini, HCL, Tech Mahindra, Accenture, IBM, L&T,** and others regularly visit the campus for recruitment.\n   - **Average Package**: The average package for engineering graduates typically ranges from **3.5 LPA to 5 LPA**.\n   - **Highest Package**: The highest package offered to students has been around **10 LPA to 12 LPA** in recent years, depending on the profile and company.\n\n### 2. **Placement Support**\n   - NIEC has a dedicated **Training and Placement Cell** that organizes **workshops, mock interviews, and aptitude training** to prepare students for placements.\n   - The college also conducts **industry visits, guest lectures, and seminars** to bridge the gap between academics and industry requirements.\n\n### 3. **Programs with Good Placements**\n   - **Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)** and **Information Technology (IT)** tend to have the highest placement rates and better packages due to the demand for tech roles.\n   - **Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Civil Engineering,** and **Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)** also see decent placements, especially in core companies and IT firms.\n\n### 4. **Factors Affecting Placement**\n   - **Academic Performance**: Students with a strong academic record and technical skills tend to secure better placements.\n   - **Skill Development**: Proficiency in programming languages, software tools, and soft skills plays a crucial role.\n   - **Internships**: Students with prior internship experience often have an edge during placements.\n\n### 5. **Alumni Network**\n   - NIEC has a growing alumni network, and many alumni work in reputed companies, which helps in leveraging connections for placements.\n\n### Conclusion\nWhile NIEC may not be among the top-tier engineering colleges in India, it does provide decent placement opportunities, especially for students who actively participate in skill development and placement activities. If you are considering NIEC, focus on building your technical skills, networking, and taking advantage of the resources provided by the college's placement cell.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
